title: Complete Blood Count (CBC)
description: A CBC test measures the levels of different components of blood such as red blood cells, white blood cells, hemoglobin, and platelets.

title: Lipid Profile Test
description: This test measures your cholesterol levels, including HDL, LDL, and triglycerides, to assess cardiovascular health.

title: Thyroid Function Test
description: This test measures the levels of thyroid hormones in the blood to diagnose thyroid disorders.

title: Liver Function Test
description: A liver function test measures enzymes and proteins in the blood to check the health of your liver.

title: Urine Analysis
description: Urine analysis is used to detect a wide range of disorders, including urinary tract infections, kidney disease, and diabetes.

title: X-Ray
description: An X-ray test is used to create images of the inside of your body to diagnose fractures, infections, or other issues.
